# Nython

**Nython** is a lightweight, visual nodeâ€‘based editor built with [DearPyGui](https://github.com/hoffstadt/DearPyGui).  
It lets you create simple data flows by dragging nodes and connecting their inputs/outputs.  The project is intentionally small â€“ itâ€™s a learning playground for DearPyGuiâ€™s node editor primitives and Python integration.

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Node creation** | Press `Shift+N` (or use the â€œCreate Nodeâ€ modal) to add a new node. Each node comes with an *Input* and *Output* attribute. |
| **Linking / unlinking** | Drag from one nodeâ€™s output to another nodeâ€™s input to create a link; drag back or press `Delete` to remove it. |
| **Keyboard shortcuts** | `Ctrl+S` â€“ save (placeholder), `Shift+N` â€“ open createâ€‘node dialog, `Delete` â€“ delete selected links/nodes. |
| **Custom theming** | Themes are defined in `ui/theming.py`.  Feel free to tweak the colors and fonts. |
| **Modular architecture** | The UI logic lives in `ui/`, while runtime flow handling is abstracted into `_runtime/`. |

> *Note:* Persistence (save/load) is a TODO â€“ you can extend the `Flow` class in `_runtime/flow.py`.

