## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Nython.git
cd Nython

# Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended)
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # Windows: .venv\\Scripts\\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Running the Application

```bash
python app.py
```

A window titled **â€œNython Editorâ€** will appear. Use the menu bar or keyboard shortcuts to interact with nodes.

### Quick Keyboard Cheatâ€‘Sheet

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `Shift+N` | Open â€œCreate Nodeâ€ modal |
| `Delete` | Delete selected node/link |
| `Ctrl+S` | (Future) Save current flow |

